diff --git a/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md b/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..efa660d4
--- /dev/null
+++ b/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md
@@ -0,0 +1,83 @@
+# C++20 Modules: Sidecar-Based Cache Coherence
+
+Replaces the current `hash_binary_file(pcm)` approach (commit `9f34fc7b`)
+which over-invalidates whenever PCM bytes drift (Conan paths, source
+absolute paths, recipe revisions). New approach: each module producer
+emits a `<pcm>.ccache-meta` sidecar containing the producer compile's
+`result_key`. Consumers fold the sidecar's `result_key` into their hash
+instead of hashing PCM bytes.
+
+Invariant: the consumer cache key changes whenever any input that
+semantically affects the PCM's emitted code changes. Path-only changes
+in the PCM bytes do not invalidate consumers.
+
+## Stage 1: argsinfo + arg detection
+**Goal**: ccache recognises module producer compiles.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- New `argsinfo.output_pcm` field set when `-fmodule-output=<path>` appears
+  (after `@`-file expansion), with optional surrounding quotes stripped.
+**Tests**: unit test in `unittest/test_argprocessing.cpp` checking the
+field is populated for representative CMake/clang command lines.
+**Status**: Not Started
+
+## Stage 2: sidecar module
+**Goal**: standalone `ModuleSidecar` with parse/format/staleness check.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- `module_sidecar.{hpp,cpp}` with `read(pcm_path)` returning optional
+  struct, `write(pcm_path, result_key)` writing tmp+rename atomically.
+- Sidecar format: `result_key=<hex>\npcm_size=<bytes>\npcm_mtime_ns=<n>\n`.
+- `matches_pcm()` validates `(pcm_size, pcm_mtime_ns)` against current stat.
+**Tests**: round-trip; staleness on size mismatch; staleness on mtime
+mismatch; missing file returns nullopt.
+**Status**: Not Started
+
+## Stage 3: consumer-side fail-closed
+**Goal**: replace existing `-fmodule-file=` byte-hash with sidecar fold +
+fail-closed on absence.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- In `hash_argument`, on `-fmodule-file=`: read sidecar; if present and
+  matches stat, fold `result_key` into hash; if absent or stale, return
+  `Statistic::could_not_use_module_sidecar`.
+- New stats counter for tracking.
+**Tests**:
+- Hit when sidecar valid.
+- Fail-closed (cache miss recorded) when sidecar absent.
+- Fail-closed when sidecar present but stale (PCM modified).
+- Hit *across PCM byte differences* when sidecar `result_key` is stable.
+**Status**: Not Started
+
+## Stage 4: producer-side caching
+**Goal**: cache the `.pcm` as a secondary output of the producer compile;
+synthesise sidecar on every cache hit and miss.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- `Result` includes `output_pcm` when set.
+- On miss after compile: `.pcm` cached; sidecar synthesised.
+- On hit replay: secondary outputs (`.pcm`) restored before primary `.o`,
+  each via tmp+rename; sidecar synthesised after `.pcm` is in place.
+**Tests**:
+- Producer hit → `.pcm` reappears with identical bytes.
+- Producer hit → sidecar present and valid.
+- Crash-during-replay simulation: `.o` mtime never advances if `.pcm`
+  failed to land (drop-write fault injection).
+**Status**: Not Started
+
+## Stage 5: end-to-end
+**Goal**: original failing test passes; new tests for path-drift and
+stale-PCM scenarios.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- `test/suites/cxx20_modules.bash` extended:
+  - layout-change test (existing) still passes.
+  - **new**: path-drift test (build PCM at `/tmp/A`, then at `/tmp/B`,
+    consumer should HIT both times if `result_key` unchanged) — proves
+    over-invalidation fixed.
+  - **new**: stale-PCM test (mutate `.pcm` directly without ccache;
+    consumer should fail-closed) — proves correctness preserved.
+**Status**: Not Started
+
+## Stage 6: docs + upstreamability
+**Goal**: ready for upstream PR.
+**Success Criteria**:
+- `doc/manual.adoc` updated.
+- `MANUAL.adoc` describes new statistic counter.
+- News entry.
+**Status**: Not Started
